@node SCRIPTCOMMANDS "Scripting Commands"

@{i}A script is a text file of DOS commands which can be executed with
the Execute command (q.v.).  The following commands are generally used
in script files to control the execution of commands in such files.@{ui}

      @{b}@{fg highlight}SCRIPTCOMMANDS@{fg text}@{ub}
      ---------------------------------------------------
      @{" Ask                                               " link Ask}
      @{" Echo                                              " link Echo}
      @{" Else                                              " link Else}
      @{" EndIf                                             " link EndIf}
      @{" EndSkip                                           " link EndSkip}
      @{" FailAt                                            " link FailAt}
      @{" If                                                " link If}
      @{" Lab                                               " link Lab}
      @{" Quit                                              " link Quit}
      @{" Skip                                              " link Skip}

      Other script commands (put at beginning):
      .KEY {args}  - indicates arguments to be used
                     in the script, surrounded by <>
      .BRA {       - or other symbol to replace ""<""
      .KET }       - or other symbol to replace "">""

      @{" See also:  Break, Wait, and the files in S:       " link Break}

@endnode

